`,e.jsxs(n.p,{children:["The ",e.jsx(n.code,{children:"default"})," group is not like other rsgroups in that it is dynamic. Its server list mirrors the current state of the cluster; i.e. if you shutdown a server that was part of the ",e.jsx(n.code,{children:"default"})," rsgroup, and then do a ",e.jsx(n.em,{children:"get_rsgroup"})," ",e.jsx(n.code,{children:"default"})," to list its content in the shell, the server will no longer be listed. For non-default groups, though a mode may be offline, it will persist in the non-default group's list of servers. But if you move the offline server from the non-default rsgroup to default, it will not show in the ",e.jsx(n.code,{children:"default"})," list. It will just be dropped."]}),`
